The Master Checklist
Graph 1 (S&P 500): Log Scale, Black Line, 1950 Start, Minor horizontal gridlines visible.

Graph 2 (Net Liquidity): Shaded Level (Blue alpha) + Blue YoY% Line + Green/Red fills for positive/negative growth.

Graph 3 (Real M2): Shaded Level (Purple alpha) + Purple YoY% Line + Teal/Orange fills for positive/negative growth.

Graph 4 (HY Spread): Both Shaded Level and Black Z-Score Line must be Inverted (Higher = Tighter/Better).

Graph 5 (Real Rates): Both Real 10Y (TIPS) and Real 3M Bill (Bill - CPI YoY) must be visible.

Graph 6 (Yield Curve): 10Y-2Y Spread + Red/Green fills for inversion.

Graph 7 (USD): Trade Weighted USD Index line.

Graph 8 (Funding/VIX): Blue Funding Stress line + Red VIX line (on twin axis).

Graph 9 (Leverage): Systemic Leverage Z-score (Orange) with min_periods=500 to ensure it starts before 2025.

Global Requirements:

Year labels on the bottom of every single chart.

Gray Recession shading on every single chart.

Anti-Crash: If Yahoo Finance rate-limits us, the app must switch to FRED S&P 500 data (starting in 2014) instead of showing an error.